            "answer_text": "If a+b=c and b+c=a\u2026bythen we should understand that a=c and after substituting we see b as \u2026 So a+c\u2260b Explanation: Let a+b=c be equ A\u2026and b+c=a be equ B So,b=c-a \u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014(1) Sustitute (1) in equ B 2c=2a\u2026 and a=c. \u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014(2) Substitute 2 in any equ either A or B We get b as 0 So b=0\u2026 So if 2 equal numbers adds and you get a 0 is only possible when those 2 equal numbers are also 0\u2019s so if a=c=0 then a+c=b\u2026 Nor else\u2026. Me signing off\u2026. ",
